# .publish-exclude
#
# List paths (relative to repo root) to strip when publishing to the public mirror.
# One path per line. Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
#
# The publish script removes known-sensitive dotfiles/dotfolders (e.g., .env,
# .github, .specify, .instructions, .pre-commit-config.yaml) automatically.
# Essential dotfiles like .gitignore, .gitattributes, .editorconfig, .nvmrc,
# and .dockerignore are preserved. You only need to list repo-specific private
# paths here.
#
# Copy this file to .publish-exclude and customize for your repo.

# --- Private or internal directories ---
# specs
# state
# logs
# memory
# hooks
# test-results
# coverage
# .private
# .certs

# --- Draft or internal documentation ---
# docs/internal
# docs/drafts

# --- Build or generated output ---
# dist
# build
# obj
# bin
